          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What makes a USP weak?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>A USP is weak if any competitor can credibly say the same thing. "High quality," "great customer service," "easy to use," and "affordable prices" are all table-stakes claims, not USPs. A strong USP requires a specific, quantified, or demonstrably unique claim.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

